# Claude Code Rules for Carnivore Weekly
# This file contains project-specific instructions and preferences

## Project Context
This is carnivoreweekly.com - a weekly newsletter analyzing trending carnivore diet content from YouTube.
- **Website:** https://carnivoreweekly.com
- **Tech Stack:** Python, Jinja2, Claude AI, YouTube API
- **Deployment:** GitHub Pages (auto-deploys from /public folder)

## User Preferences
- **Design Philosophy:** Clean, minimal, avoid over-engineering
- **Emoji Usage:** Minimal - only when explicitly requested, prefer custom images/icons
- **Commit Messages:** Include "ü§ñ Generated with Claude Code" footer
- **Communication Style:** Direct, concise, professional - avoid excessive praise

## Automation
- **Weekly Update:** Runs every Monday via GitHub Actions
  - Fetches latest YouTube videos
  - Generates AI-powered content analysis
  - Creates newsletter
  - Auto-commits and deploys

